sliderule minimal-build workarounds for the zagg h5coro benchmark shim
(issue #149 phase 3). Applies with `patch -p1` at the sliderule source root;
generated against sliderule v5.4.3 (ce4be309, 2026-06-16).

Benchmark-only change:
  * Asset.h — the Asset constructor and attributes_t sit in the class's single
    private: section; the shim constructs an Asset directly (lua_State* == NULL,
    which LuaObject tolerates), so that section becomes public.

Minimal-build fixes (core does not compile with the aws/geo/... packages OFF;
upstream evidently always builds with them ON):
  * core/CMakeLists.txt — OutputLib.cpp uses uuid/uuid.h but only the geo
    package links libuuid; link it in core.
  * DeduplicateRunner.cpp — unguarded #include "GeoLib.h" (geo pkg), unused.
  * EndpointObject.cpp — unguarded #include "SecretManager.h" (aws pkg); all
    uses already sit under #ifdef __aws__.
  * RequestParameters.cpp — samplers (FieldMap<GeoFields>) is declared under
    #ifdef __geo__ in the header but used unguarded in the .cpp; guard the
    three sampler lua methods, their meta-table entries, and the sampler
    branches of luaExport/luaEncode.

